From:Paul Senior
Dan Meleney. Have you looked at NNN.to that's been mentioned here? Does that
one meet your requirements?

http://finance.yahoo.com/q?s=NEYYF.PK

2pv10 = US$7.73 or US$476M. ("NiMin reserves are from Huddleston & Co., Inc. NI
51-101 reserve report effective January 1, 2010")

These dinky e&p companies always seem to be updating their balance sheet for
shares or debt. As of July, I believe there are 83M fully-diluted shares,
current cash of C$19M and debt of C36M.

NNN.To stock price is C$1.02, so enterprise value might conservatively be
viewed as $1.02x83M, -19M + 36M = $102M

So as I view it, the gas/oil asset (apparently 96% oil) to enterprise value is
476/102 or over 4:1. That's a pretty tough ratio to beat given the several
other e&p stocks I am looking at and buying.
