For example in the Cooperate summary, they value the 11.9M BOE at 215M$
(18.1$/BOE) and the 27.9M$ proved+ probable reserves as 476M$ (17.1$/BOE). So i
wonder if they include the Capex that is surely needed to develop probable
reserves into proved ones. Last time I checked, oil does not bubble out of the
ground when you put a stick in the ground <g>.
http://www.niminenergy.com/i/pdf/NiminPresentation.pdf

