Date:8/18/2010 11:28:32 AM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
You are 100% correct. TIP does not fully protect from interest rate risk, since
the interest rates are not fully correlated with inflation. In other words,
interest rate could rise to 6-7% with almost no inflation.

On the other hand TIP maturity distribution is pretty even on the maturity
scale. So it's not like buying 15 or 30 year bonds flat. :) Short term
maturities is a protection against interest rate risk. Again, this is only
partial protection and you pay for it with lower yields.
